    "notes_label_1": "Design Notes",
    "notes_1": "New version based on DRC without chocolate - see google drive file Dark Mild Recipe w/DRC\r\nFor the initial version, no coloring grains till we see what the DRC does, then consider some midnight wheat for coloring per the above document.\r\n- similar water chemistry to previous tries, just a little less Na (5 ppm). Target ph still 5.4\r\n- plan to use new thermometer and measure bed temps - this may be the one - see process on the wall\r\n- heat sparge to 170 and let it cool from there as we sparge - don't want water to be over 170 during sparge itself (no tannin extraction at this temp), per Google, over sparging isn't possible with a 1 gallon sparge int this beer (tannins come from over sparging, not letting the basket drip into the kettle too long)\r\n\r\n** worth noting - this was 2023 crop year hops with no adjustments for age - something to remember when we get fresh hops **",
    "notes_label_2": "Process Notes",
    "notes_2": "Ensure sparge water is no more than 170F to avoid tannins\r\nonly process change will be to dry hop at 85% attenuation for 2 days per my guidelines\r\nDry hop with 2 bolts should be more than enough!\r\nBurst carbonate at 30psi for ~15 hours, then pull PRV, put on serving pressure for 12 hours\r\nFine tune carbonation to 2.1 volumes",
