        "observed_color": "light brown, srm 14-15?",
        "brew_day_notes": "everything according to plans,  mash temps 152-154 (confirming this time is anvil is low by 1 degree), ph = 5.3 + 1 correction = 5.4 (on target), sparge water under 170F, volume 2.6-2.7 gallons in fermenter, measured OG 8.5B / 1034 or 1033 by tilt. Yeast from starter ~120B versus need of 65B. More mash info in Next Anvil Brew Day.docx.\nDry hop 85% target is 1013-1014; dry hopped Wednesday midnight with 2 bolts, 1015-1016 by tilt, 1014 by refractometer.\nReached cold crash temps, sat, 5/14 ~8 PM\nKeg Mon 6/15 11:30 PM (ok, a day less cold crash than planned but club meeting tomorrow), tilt 1010, 4.9B = 1.010\nDone Tues 6/16 5PM",
        "tasting_notes": "nice beer, good body and carbonation, pleasant earthy, sweet malt aroma, nice taste in the malt backbone but caramel sweetness becomes cloying (maybe 12% crystal is way too much; Gemini says the two crystal malts are fighting each other), a little sharp, lacks a little of the dark malt character; too sweet to drink in quantity (not sessionable). Plus color is way off. If we stay on the DRC path, next up is a try without the C120 and a touch of dark malt for character.",
